# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for the libtracer_quic module tests.
#
# libmsquic.so is a prebuilt, NON-TSan-instrumented third-party library: TSan
# only sees its pthread calls through interceptors and cannot see the library's
# own internal synchronization (epoll/eventfd wakeups + C11 atomics), so
# msquic-internal accesses (QuicLookup*, CxPlatProcessEvents, ...) report as
# races that are not observable ones. Suppress races whose racy access lives in
# the library — libtracer's OWN code (transport_quic.cpp, the receivers, the
# tests) stays fully TSan-gated: any race with a libtracer frame on top still
# fails the run.
called_from_lib:libmsquic.so
